OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBen John: Judge pleased by 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fextremist's progress with  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fclassic novels             
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A man told by a judge to read classic  
OL,6, literature after being convicted of    
OL,7, possessing a bomb-making manual has    
OL,8, apparently made "encouraging" progress.
OL,10,FBen John, 21, was convicted of having a
OL,11,Fcopy of the Anarchist Cookbook on a    
OL,12,Fcomputer hard drive.                   
OL,14,FHe was given a two-year prison         
OL,15,Fsentence, suspended for two years.     
OL,17,FAt the sentencing hearing, Judge       
OL,18,FTimothy Spencer QC asked him to read   
OL,19,Fclassic literature and said he would   
OL,20,Ftest him on this at review hearings.   
